data.description: Farm house charm with large 984 sf shop, both GEOTHERMALLY heated with a hot well. Mature fruit trees, sweet seedless grape trellis shading your back patio, irrigated garden beds, and tons of storage.  Open floor plan completely remodeled in 2008 and renovated again in 2023.  Hard wood floors, fireplace, fully fenced yard.  Geothermal well is only 200 feet deep and hot enough to heat the house and shop by thermo syphon (no pump needed). The City water comes on to property, T's off to go down the hot well and comes back up hot.  That's your hot water heater.  Only pay for electricity of a fan to blow the hot air in the forced air geothermal system. Attics of house and shop have ply wood floors for additional storage areas.
